xoaFvd-okFL4mcRMeKfmZ04lu7qZuQ==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating daemon threads**\\n\\nI see that the JVM may keep running after the assertion test unless I set the runnerThread to daemon mode. However, there’s a concern that if the Runner.run method spawns a non-daemon thread, it could lead to a hang. The Event Dispatch Thread (EDT) often remains non-daemon, but that shouldn't be problematic in Swing tests. It seems safer to set the outer thread as daemon to prevent hangs, especially if the JFrame's closure fails. Closing or disposing before rendering seems vital too.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test behaviors**\\n\\nI’m wondering if running a test without any suites is considered supported behavior. The Runner's documented public API does allow for GUI display without reporters, so reporting zero tests should be valid—which is normal. The focus here seems to be on rendering the event list. I also need to ensure that there’s no skipping of the native image and check if the active class is private but accessible through the public Runner. Lastly, confirming that there are indeed no tests under the source target seems necessary.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating potential issues**\\n\\nI’m noticing a potential issue with the JList model. If its size is greater than 0 but the event reflects MotionToSuppress, it could lead to confusion, especially since RunStarting isn’t involved. I’m thinking I might need to look for direct reflections, or perhaps there are none at all. Just to be thorough, should I check the git diff? I wonder if that would clarify things or highlight any discrepancies.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_yfclCltCuXxcfNrPTktDXRpT|fc_0b67f1c04402e2e7016a2912d12cd08196b5ddfc4d1561113d", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "git diff -- tests/src/org.scalatest/scalatest-core_2.13/3.2.19/src/test/scala/org_scalatest/scalatest_core_2_13/IconEmbellishedListCellRendererInnerIconsTest.scala", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2600, "output": 855, "cacheRead": 52224, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 55679, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781076660313, "responseId": "resp_0b67f1c04402e2e7016a2912b4ee408196aee2771f4e6434a9"}}
